column2: Please list the year and country during which the race is held on circuits in Shanghai.
column3: Shanghai is a name of location;
column4: SELECT T2.year, T1.country FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE T1.location = 'Shanghai'
column6:
SELECT T2.year, T3.country 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId
    JOIN llm_circuits AS T3 ON T1.location = T3.location
    WHERE T1.location = 'Shanghai'

column2: Where can the introduction of the races held on Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya be found?
column3: introduction of races refers to url; Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya is a name of circuit;
column4: SELECT DISTINCT T1.url FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE T1.name = 'Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya'
column6:
SELECT DISTINCT T3.url 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId 
    JOIN llm_circuits AS T3 ON T1.location = T3.location AND T1.name = T3.name
    WHERE T1.name = 'Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya'

column2: How many races in the year 2010 are held on grand prixs outside Asia and Europe?
column4: SELECT COUNT(T3.raceId) FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T3 ON T3.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE T1.country NOT IN ( 'Bahrain', 'China', 'Singapore', 'Japan', 'Korea', 'Turkey', 'UAE', 'Malaysia', 'Spain', 'Monaco', 'Azerbaijan', 'Austria', 'Belgium', 'France', 'Germany', 'Hungary', 'Italy', 'UK' ) AND T3.year = 2010
column6:
SELECT COUNT(T2.raceId) 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId 
    JOIN llm_circuits AS T3 ON T1.location = T3.location
    WHERE T3.country NOT IN ( 'Bahrain', 'China', 'Singapore', 'Japan', 'Korea', 'Turkey', 'UAE', 'Malaysia', 'Spain', 'Monaco', 'Azerbaijan', 'Austria', 'Belgium', 'France', 'Germany', 'Hungary', 'Italy', 'UK' ) 
    AND T2.year = 2010

column2: Which country is the constructor which got 1 point in the race No. 24 from?
column3: race number refers to raceId;

column2: For the driver who had the Q2 time as 0:01:40 in the qualifying race No. 355, what is his nationality?
column3: race number refers to raceId;
column4: SELECT DISTINCT T2.nationality FROM qualifying AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId WHERE T1.raceId = 355 AND T1.q2 LIKE '1:40%'
column6:
SELECT DISTINCT T3.nationality 
    FROM qualifying AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId 
    JOIN llm_people AS T3 ON T2.forename || T2.surname = T3.name
    WHERE T1.raceId = 355 AND T1.q2 LIKE '1:40%'

column2: Show me the season page of year when the race No. 901 took place.
column3: race number refers to raceId;
column4: SELECT T2.url FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN seasons AS T2 ON T2.year = T1.year WHERE T1.raceId = 901
column6:
SELECT T3.season_url 
    FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN seasons AS T2 ON T2.year = T1.year 
    JOIN llm_races AS T3 ON T1.name = T3.name AND T1.year = T3.year
    WHERE T1.raceId = 901

column2: For all the drivers who finished the game in race No. 592, who is the top 3 oldest?
column3: drivers who finished the race refers to time is not empty; oldest driver refers to oldest dob;
column4: SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId WHERE T2.raceId = 592 AND T2.time IS NOT NULL AND T1.dob IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T1.dob ASC LIMIT 3
column6:
SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname 
    FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId 
    JOIN llm_people AS T3 ON T1.forename || T1.surname = T3.name
    WHERE T2.raceId = 592 AND T2.time IS NOT NULL AND T3.dob IS NOT NULL 
    ORDER BY T3.dob ASC LIMIT 3

column2: Who was the player that got the lap time of 0:01:27 in the race No. 161? Show his introduction website.

column6:
SELECT DISTINCT T2.forename, T2.surname, T3.person_url 
    FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId 
    JOIN llm_people AS T3 ON T2.forename || T2.surname = T3.name
    WHERE T1.raceId = 161 AND T1.time LIKE '1:27%'

column2: For the drivers who took part in the race in 1983/7/16, what's their race completion rate?
column3: DIVIDE(COUNT(driverid where time has value and date = '1983-07-16'), (COUNT(driverid where date = '1983-07-16')) as percentage
column4: SELECT CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN T2.time IS NOT NULL THEN T2.driverId END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T2.driverId) FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.raceId = T1.raceId WHERE T1.date = '1983-07-16'
column6:
SELECT CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN T2.time IS NOT NULL THEN T2.driverId END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T2.driverId) 
    FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.raceId = T1.raceId 
    INNER JOIN llm_races AS T3 ON T3.year = T1.year AND T3.name = T1.name
    WHERE T1.year = 1983 AND T3.date = '1983-07-16'

column2: For the driver who set the fastest lap speed, what is his nationality?

the fastest lap speed refers to (MAX) fastestLapSpeed

SQL mentions raceId = 348, that is not in the question

column6:

column2: Name the first race recorded. What are the other races that happened within the same month and year of that race.
column3: the first race refers to year = year(min(date)) and month = month(min(date));
column4: SELECT name FROM races WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', date) = ( SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', date) FROM races ORDER BY date ASC LIMIT 1 ) AND STRFTIME('%m', date) = ( SELECT STRFTIME('%m', date) FROM races ORDER BY date ASC LIMIT 1 )
column6:
SELECT T1.name 
    FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN llm_races AS T2 ON T2.year = T1.year AND T2.name = T1.name
    WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T2.date) = ( 
            SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', T4.date) 
                FROM races AS T3 INNER JOIN llm_races AS T4 ON T3.year = T4.year AND T3.name = T4.name
                ORDER BY T4.date ASC LIMIT 1 
        ) 
    AND STRFTIME('%m', T2.date) = ( 
            SELECT STRFTIME('%m', T6.date) 
            FROM races AS T5 INNER JOIN llm_races AS T6 ON T5.year = T6.year AND T5.name = T6.name
            ORDER BY T6.date ASC LIMIT 1 
    )

column2: State the name and date of the last 5 rounds of race in year 1999.
column3: the last round refers to max(round);
column4: SELECT name, date FROM races WHERE year = 1999 ORDER BY round DESC LIMIT 5
column6:
SELECT T1.name, T2.date 
    FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN llm_races AS T2 ON T2.year = T1.year AND T2.name = T1.name
    WHERE T1.year = 1999 
    ORDER BY T1.round 
    DESC LIMIT 5

column2: When was the last three f1 season whereby Brands Hatch hosted the British Grand Prix?
column3: the last refers to max(year);
column4: SELECT T2.date FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE T1.name = 'Brands Hatch' AND T2.name = 'British Grand Prix' ORDER BY T2.year DESC LIMIT 3
column6:
SELECT T3.date 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId
    INNER JOIN llm_races AS T3 ON T2.year = T3.year AND T2.name = T3.name
    WHERE T1.name = 'Brands Hatch' AND T2.name = 'British Grand Prix' 
    ORDER BY T2.year DESC LIMIT 3

column2: Name the top 10 driver with the most winning. Mention his nationality and what is his average point scores.
column3: the most winning refers to MAX(COUNT(wins)); avg(points);
column4: SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname, T1.nationality, AVG(T2.points) FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN driverStandings AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId WHERE T2.wins = 1 GROUP BY T1.forename, T1.surname, T1.nationality ORDER BY COUNT(T2.wins) DESC LIMIT 10
column6:
SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname, T3.nationality, AVG(T2.points) 
    FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN driverStandings AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId 
    JOIN llm_people AS T3 ON T1.forename || T1.surname = T3.name
    WHERE T2.wins = 1 
    GROUP BY T1.forename, T1.surname, T3.nationality 
    ORDER BY COUNT(T2.wins) DESC LIMIT 10

column2: How old is the youngest 8 Japanese driver? What are their names?
column3: youngest Japanese driver refers to max(dob); Japanese refers to nationality = 'Japanese'; age = 2022-year(dob)+1
column4: SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', dob), forename , surname FROM drivers WHERE nationality = 'Japanese' ORDER BY dob DESC LIMIT 8
column6:
SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T2.dob), T1.forename , T1.surname 
    FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN llm_people AS T2 ON T1.forename || T1.surname = T2.name
    WHERE T2.nationality = 'Japanese' 
    ORDER BY T2.dob 
    DESC LIMIT 8

column2: List circuits which host 4 f1 races from year 1990 to 2000.
column3: from year 1990 to 2000 refers to year(date) between 1990 and 2000;
column4: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T2.date) BETWEEN '1990' AND '2000' GROUP BY T1.name HAVING COUNT(T2.raceId) = 4
column6:
SELECT DISTINCT T1.name 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId 
    INNER JOIN llm_races AS T3 ON T2.name = T3.name AND T2.year = T3.year
    WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T3.date) BETWEEN '1990' AND '2000' 
    GROUP BY T1.name HAVING COUNT(T2.raceId) = 4

column2: List circuits in USA which hosted f1 races in 2006. State the name and location of circuit and the name of the race it hosted.
column4: SELECT T1.name, T1.location, T2.name FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId WHERE T1.country = 'USA' AND T2.year = 2006
column6:
SELECT T1.name, T1.location, T2.name 
    FROM circuits AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T2.circuitID = T1.circuitId 
    JOIN llm_circuits AS T3 ON T1.location = T3.location AND T1.name = T3.name
    WHERE T3.country = 'USA' AND T2.year = 2006
